==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Sod
<hw>Sod</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Akin to LG. <ets>sode</ets>, D.
<ets>zode</ets>, OD. <ets>sode</ets>, <ets>soode</ets>, OFries. satha,
and E. <ets>seethe</ets>. So named from its <ets>sodden</ets> state in
wet weather. See <er>Seethe</er>.]</ety> <def>That stratum of the
surface of the soil which is filled with the roots of grass, or any
portion of that surface; turf; sward.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She there shall dress a sweeter <qex>sod</qex>⟦br⟧
Than Fancy's feet have ever trod.</q> <rj><qau>Collins.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sod</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Sod
<hw>Sod</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Sodden</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Sodding</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To cover with sod; to
turf.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

